   <concept id="FAR_17_109" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">17.109</ph> Contract clauses.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1048e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1076e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            The contracting officer shall insert the clause at <xref href="52.217-2.dita#FAR_52_217_2"
                        base="i1057120"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.217-2</xref>, Cancellation Under Multi-year Contracts, in solicitations and contracts when a multi-year contract is contemplated.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1076e18">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Economic price adjustment clauses</i>. Economic price adjustment clauses are adaptable to multi-year contracting needs. When the period of production is likely to warrant a labor and material costs contingency in the contract price, the contracting officer should normally use an economic price adjustment clause (see <xref href="16.203.dita#FAR_16_203"
                        base="i1104876"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">16.203</xref>). When contracting for services, the contracting officer-</p>
               <ol id="d1048e41" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1076e29">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
								                Shall add the clause at <xref href="52.222-43.dita#FAR_52_222_43"
                              base="i1056443"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-43</xref>, Fair Labor Standards Act and Service Contract Labor Standards- Price Adjustment (Multiple Year and Option Contracts), when the contract includes the clause at <xref href="52.222-41.dita#FAR_52_222_41"
                              base="i1056332"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-41</xref>, Service Contract Labor Standards;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1076e40">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
								                May modify the clause at <xref href="52.222-43.dita#FAR_52_222_43"
                              base="i1056443"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-43</xref> in overseas contracts when laws, regulations, or international agreements require contractors to pay higher wage rates; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1076e48">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
								                May use an economic price adjustment clause authorized by <xref href="16.203.dita#FAR_16_203"
                              base="i1104876"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">16.203</xref>, when potential fluctuations require coverage and are not included in cost contingencies provided for by the clause at <xref href="52.222-43.dita#FAR_52_222_43"
                              base="i1056443"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-43</xref>.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
